The paper discusses the architecture of recurrent neural networks and their ability to adapt to input sequences by adjusting the computation time. This topic falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), natural language processing (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given that the paper focuses on comparing two architectures for recurrent neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses the application of these architectures to natural language processing and computer vision tasks, cs.CL and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories.
